servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/toasted-rice-bowl-5797acc092eec92d738b4568
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
---

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the @basmati rice{3/4%cup} and stir continuously, ~{2-3%minutes}, until golden brown.

> Be careful not to burn the rice.

Cook the rice: Add the remaining rice and @water{1 1/2%cups} to the pot. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer for about ~{15%minutes}, until tender.

Wash and dry all produce. Core, seed, and thinly slice the @red bell pepper{1}(thinly sliced). Mince or grate the @garlic{2%clove}(minced or grated). Thinly slice the @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), keeping the greens and whites separate. Cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Chop the @shrimp{10%ounce} into 1/2-inch pieces. Shuck the @corn on the cob{1}, then cut the kernels off the cob.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper, scallion whites, garlic, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon}(pinch) to the pan. Cook, tossing, ~{5-7%minutes}, until tender. Add the shrimp to the pan. Cook, tossing, ~{1-2%minutes}, until cooked through. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Fluff the rice with a #fork{} and add to the pan along with the corn, scallion greens, and @soy sauce{3%teaspoon}. Cook, tossing, for ~{1%minute}. Season with salt and pepper.

Serve the toasted shrimp rice bowl with a wedge of lime and enjoy!